          "body": "Ezekiel 37 begins with a problem that is more than political. Verse 11 quotes Israel directly: *Our bones are dried up and our hope has perished. We are completely cut off.* The exiles by the Chebar canal have done the math. The northern kingdom fell to Assyria in 722 BC and never returned. Jerusalem fell to Babylon in 586 BC; the temple is rubble; the Davidic line is in chains. The covenant promises — land, dynasty, presence — appear to have died with the nation. The chapter is not designed for healthy bones. It is designed for a people who have rightly concluded that natural recovery is impossible, and who need to hear that *natural* is not the only category God works in."
